            "content": [
              {
                "nodeType": "text",
                "value": "Years of sitting by the hearth or old injuries from a cart mishap have left this character\u2019s joints creaky and stubborn. They groan like an old oak when rising from a chair, and a quick sidestep is out of the question. Village children giggle as they hobble after a runaway piglet. Flexibility is a fond memory for them.",
